President Donald J. Trump addressed the United Nations General Assembly (UNGA) and highlighted the progress made in dealing with threats from North Korea, Iran, and ISIS. The historic Singapore Summit with North Korean Chairman Kim Jong-Un resulted in a commitment to denuclearize the Korean peninsula. The Trump Administration also changed the rules of engagement against ISIS, leading to significant territorial losses for the group. President Trump withdrew the United States from the Iran nuclear deal and called for a new agreement that addresses Iran's support for terrorism. The President emphasized the need for strong, sovereign nations to work together to confront threats to civilization.